Subject:    Who's the root?
From:       <a href="?a=95837693400019&r=1&w=2">MOCKAPETRIS () USC-ISIB ! ARPA</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198510">1985-10-31 13:54:38</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426588&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426588&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Several people have sent me messages asking for the current identities of
root servers and asking what possible alternative there is to the
999999999999999999 entries.

To find out who all of the root servers are, ask any root server.  They
are currently ISIB, ISIC, SRI-NIC and BRL-AOS.  In an implementation I'd
suggest that you might wire in say SRI-NIC and maybe another, but that you
periodically go back and get the latest info.  In any case, treat the
wired in data as a last resort, and never distribute it in answer to
queries.  With any luck, you will never have to use the wired in data
more than once.

paul
